{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5182ffec-68fb-4cc3-bab5-7e0b1f64906e","content":"Good news — with .NET 10, `dotnet test` uses Microsoft Testing Platform **by default**. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property was the .NET 9 opt-in and is now redundant. You can safely remove it.\n\nYour project already has `EnableMSTestRunner` (which makes MSTest produce an MTP executable), so you just need to drop the extra property:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_015HaFRxkdxzRHPcFAUXHTEd","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Removing redundant property"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01JVyvhNgoeRQNbxKrkrZsSV","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-74f7f3f8efc44be3a122e88477cacfea/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n","new_str":"\n"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-74f7f3f8efc44be3a122e88477cacfea/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"9c26a1df-6076-45e0-9fbc-9ee25cafc439","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK (10.0.100) and wants to know about native MTP support. Let me explain:\n\nIn .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) as the default test runner. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property was needed in .NET 9 to opt into MTP support with `dotnet test`, but in .NET 10, this is the default behavior, so that property is no longer needed.\n\nLet me also check the current state - with .NET 10, the `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property is redundant since MTP is the default. They can safely remove it.\n\n\nNow I'll update their project file to remove the unnecessary property.","outputTokens":468,"requestId":"0C00:69BE5:48675A:54CD5B:69F00622"},"id":"47c3c5e7-7abc-44e8-a8e1-6a9f769f75d1","timestamp":"2026-04-28T00:58:19.122Z","parentId":"5f829a85-485a-4550-956c-ea8317ea6b0b"}
